        <item>
            <title>全球最细吸尘机破健力士纪录   印度学生用一支原子笔制作</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2024/09/12/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen/fun-tech/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2024/09/12/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen/fun-tech/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Thu, 12 Sep 2024 10:00:59 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[科技新闻]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[健力士]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[健力士世界纪录]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[吸尘机]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1262499</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>近日一名 23 岁印度工程学学生以一支原子笔为基础，成功制造出全球最细的吸尘器，打破了健力士世界纪录。这「部」全球最细的吸尘机展示了如何利用日常物品转化为实用科技产品，为环保和科技界注入了全新灵感。</p><p>根据健力士世界纪录的量度方式（手柄、电源线等不计算在内），这款吸尘器主体最短轴仅有 0.65 厘米长，比手指尾指甲更细。不要看它机仔细细，其设有吸入口和尘埃收集装置，并可透过 USB 供电。这款吸尘器设计虽然轻巧，但功能强大，能有效清理微尘和碎屑，特别适合清洁键盘及汽车内饰等狭窄空间。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1262513" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912152504-694x454.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="454" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912152504-694x454.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912152504.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2024/9/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen">Guiness World Records</a></p><p>凭一支原子笔打破全球最细吸尘机世界纪录的学生名叫 Tapala Nadamuni ，其表示他目标是透过日常用品，设计新颖又实用的工具。Tapala Nadamuni 指，虽然吸尘器外形看似平平无奇，但其内部机制经过精心设计，实际使用时具有一定清洁能力。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1262514" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912153842-694x454.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="454" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912153842-694x454.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912153842.jpg 1278w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2024/9/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen">Guiness World Records</a></p><p>根据健力士世界纪录对吸尘机的定义，吸尘机应为一种透过内部负压产生吸力以拾取碎片的电动装置（ an electrically powered device which picks up debris with suction resulting from a negative internal pressure.）Tapala Nadamuni 表示，设计时遇到的难题是怎样在如此细小的机身产生足够吸起碎片的吸力。Tapala Nadamuni 打破世界纪录的吸尘机主要材料为一支普通可换芯原子笔，另外加入了些少塑胶和金属，总成本约为 2 万印度卢比（约港币 1,856 元）。吸尘机内设由 4 Volt 震动摩打推动的微型风扇，以产生吸力。当用家连接电源后，吸尘机会随即启动。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1262515" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912154525-694x456.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="456" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912154525-694x456.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/20240912154525.jpg 1275w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2024/9/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen">Guiness World Records</a></p><p>健力士世界纪录审核团队最终确认这款吸尘器是目前「全球最细吸尘机」。据印度媒体报道，Tapala Nadamuni 希望他的发明能鼓励更多人参与创新设计，并展示如何以低成本实现高效能的成果。Tapala Nadamuni 又指，发明不一定需要依赖昂贵的材料或复杂的技术，只要运用创意，日常物品亦能转变成惊人的工具。</p><p>资料来源：<a href="https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2024/9/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen">Guiness World Records</a>、<a href="https://www.ndtv.com/offbeat/indian-student-makes-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-from-a-simple-pen-6504476">NDTV</a>、<a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/indian-student-sets-guinness-world-record-with-the-worlds-smallest-vacuum-leaner/articleshow/113168956.cms">Times of India</a>、<a href="https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2024/Sep/09/23-year-old-indian-student-sets-guinness-world-record-with-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner">Indian Express</a></p><div class="post-article-block"><div class="block-main"><header><div class="line-1"></div></header></div></div><div class="post-article-block featured-image-block"></div><br /><b>相关文章:</b><blockquote><li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/09/10/youtubers-built-6-ft-tall-working-replica-of-iphone-15-pro-max/fun-tech/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">破健力士世界纪录   YouTuber 自制 6 呎高 iPhone 15 Pro</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/08/16/ibrahim-al-nasser/game-channel/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">成功连接 444 部游戏机至单一电视　沙特男子创造新健力士世界纪录</a></li>&nbsp;</blockquote><br /><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/09/12/indian-student-builds-worlds-smallest-vacuum-cleaner-using-a-pen/fun-tech/">全球最细吸尘机破健力士纪录   印度学生用一支原子笔制作</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
]]>
            </description>
